The paper discusses a method for reading research compendia, which are a form of publication that includes not only the research paper's text and figures, but also all data and software for better reproducibility. This suggests that the paper could be relevant to several sub-categories, including cs.CY (Computers and Society), which deals with the social and ethical aspects of computing; cs.DL (Digital Libraries), which focuses on the management and dissemination of digital information; cs.SE (Software Engineering), which deals with the development and maintenance of software systems; cs.DB (Databases), which focuses on the management and analysis of large datasets; and cs.IR (Information Retrieval), which deals with the retrieval and analysis of information from large datasets.
